orks, events, and alternative media. The book will introduce students and scholars to important qualitative approaches to the study of social activism within these four research sites, which is based entirely on successful research projects that have been conducted and published in recent years. Ultimately, this book will prove integral to any students and scholars who wish to use qualitative methods for their research endeavors concerning socialactivism in contemporary society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2022) 0aPolitical participation. 0aSocial action. 0aSocial change. 0aSocial movements. 4aCommunications. 4aSociology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Methodology.2bisacsh  aactivism.  aactivist networks.  aactivist organizations.  aalternative media.  aprotest.  aqualitative methods.  asocial movement.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831107290160 cprintz978082327413040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823274161?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823274161zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823274161/original  a978-3-11-072901-6 Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA